        "category": [
          {
            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-description"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a bright and curious 6-year-old girl who loves drawing colorful pictures of animals and playing pretend with her stuffed toys at home. She lives with her parents and a 9-year-old brother in a cozy suburban house. She started kindergarten this year and has thoroughly enjoyed making new friends, though her classroom recently saw several children out sick with similar complaints. {patientName} is generally an energetic child who enjoys outdoor play and dancing, but over the past two days she has been noticeably quieter and more clingy than usual.\n\n{patientName} presented to the pediatric clinic today with her mother, appearing flushed and uncomfortable. She is holding her throat and wincing slightly when swallowing, repeatedly asking for cold water. Her voice sounds slightly hoarse, and her mother reports she refused her morning breakfast because it \"hurt too much to eat.\" She has been running a low-grade fever since yesterday evening.\n\nOn physical examination, {patientName} has a temperature of 38.4 °C, heart rate of 102 bpm, and appears mildly distressed but cooperative. Oropharyngeal inspection reveals markedly erythematous posterior pharynx with mild tonsillar enlargement and scattered petechiae on the soft palate. Anterior cervical lymph nodes are palpable and slightly tender. No peritonsillar bulging is observed.\n\nAt home, {patientName} enjoys finger-painting, playing with her doll collection, and watching animated nature documentaries with her father. She attends kindergarten five days a week and recently joined a Saturday morning dance class. Her diet is generally balanced, though she has a well-known fondness for apple juice and strawberry yogurt. Her parents are very attentive and health-conscious, keeping up with her vaccination schedule diligently."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:8c3d5184-b7bd-434b-a5bb-e1f17ced66b6",
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Communication",
        "status": "completed",
