        },
        "category": [
          {
            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-history"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has no significant past medical history. She was born at full term via spontaneous vaginal delivery with no neonatal complications. Her immunization record is complete and up to date for her age. She experienced two prior episodes of viral upper respiratory tract infections in the past 18 months, both managed supportively at home without antibiotics. There is no history of recurrent streptococcal throat infections, rheumatic fever, or scarlet fever. {patientName} has no prior surgical history. She has a known allergy to penicillin (mild urticarial rash noted after a course administered at age 4), and is therefore being treated with amoxicillin under careful monitoring given the partial cross-reactivity consideration. She lives with non-smoking parents; there is no exposure to second-hand smoke in the home. She has mild seasonal allergic rhinitis managed occasionally with cetirizine."
          }
        ]
      }
